ion in insects, migrations of aquatic organisms, clutch size and parental care in birds, and movement of spiders and raptors. Advanced topics, including the study of dynamic evolutionarily stable strategies, are discussed in Part III.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAnimal behaviorxData processing. 0aAnimal behaviorxMathematical models. 0aAnimal ecologyxData processing. 0aAnimal ecologyxMathematical models. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh1 aClark, Colin Whitcomb, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691206967zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691206967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691206967.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK